                <h1>Understanding Supersonic Sound: The Science Behind Speed</h1>
                <p>Supersonic sound refers to speeds exceeding that of sound waves, which travel at approximately 343 meters per second in air. This phenomenon creates unique acoustic effects, such as sonic booms. Notably, supersonic jets and military aircraft utilize this capability to reduce travel time dramatically, revolutionizing air travel and military operations.</p>
